@SunnyXu from what you say I understand that this package is expected to work only on Windows, is that correct?  However the test here is performed on a Linux machine.  Maybe you could make your `__init__` something like
```julia
function __init__()
    @static if Sys.iswindows()
        global rrlib = Libdl.dlopen(rr_api)
        global antlib = Libdl.dlopen(antimony_api)
    else
        @warn "This platform isn't supported by RoadRunner.jl"
    end
end
```
?  In this way the user trying to use your package on a different platform will be gracefully warned, instead of causing a bad crash.  Also, this will let AutoMerge work
